@palladia you can check other place for "PAL_Free(operation->protocolConnection);" in interationprotocolhandler.c
pal_free will call systemfree which will call free which will not set it to null, Setting unused pointers to NULL is a defensive style, protecting against dangling pointer bugs.  previous logic operation->connection become unused pointer here, then when next checking in other place it is not null and can be free, then double free occurs.
next line operation also need to set to null, I will update it if no other issues, thanks.

I think you misunderstood me.  I do know what PAL_Free() does, and I do know why one sets the pointer to NULL after free.  I'm just not sure this will fix Dan's issue.  But let's wait for Dan's verification.
Anyway, if you want to be defensive, do something like:
if (operation)
{
PAL_Free(operation->protocolConnection);
operation->protocolConnection = NULL;
PAL_Free(operation);
operation = NULL;
}

